            <div class="mri-boundary-row"><span class="mri-boundary-label">External: UCSF/NYU metastasis</span><span class="mri-boundary-value">On par with prospective</span></div>
            <div class="mri-boundary-row"><span class="mri-boundary-label">External: acute stroke</span><span class="mri-boundary-value">On par with prospective</span></div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="mri-boundary-panel unknown">
          <div class="mri-boundary-header">Unknown</div>
          <div class="mri-boundary-body">
            <div class="mri-boundary-row"><span class="mri-boundary-label">Training data from</span><span class="mri-boundary-value">0 other institutions</span></div>
            <div class="mri-boundary-row"><span class="mri-boundary-label">Prospective test at</span><span class="mri-boundary-value">0 other hospitals</span></div>
            <div class="mri-boundary-row"><span class="mri-boundary-label">Community hospital protocols</span><span class="mri-boundary-value">Not tested</span></div>
            <div class="mri-boundary-row"><span class="mri-boundary-label">Disease prevalence</span><span class="mri-boundary-value">Reflects Michigan only</span></div>
            <div class="mri-boundary-row"><span class="mri-boundary-label">Out-of-distribution conditions</span><span class="mri-boundary-value">Not addressed</span></div>
            <div class="mri-boundary-row"><span class="mri-boundary-label">FDA status</span><span class="mri-boundary-value">No clearance. No submission disclosed.</span></div>
          </div>
          <div class="mri-boundary-footer">Everything validated lives inside one institution's walls. Everything outside is blank.</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p>Within U-M Health's patient population, the fairness results are strong. According to the paper, Prima showed no statistically significant performance differences across race, sex, MRI manufacturer, or insurance status. One exception: patients aged 34 to 61, where the authors attribute the disparity to diagnostic diversity in that cohort. But these fairness results prove algorithmic equity within Michigan's population. They do not prove it universally. The external validation offers partial reassurance — 98.0% Top-3 accuracy on BraTS glioma region selection, performance on par with prospective results on UCSF and NYU metastasis datasets, and competitive acute stroke detection. Transfer learning applications showed promise too: brain age estimation with 5.6 years mean absolute error, autism spectrum prediction matching independent supervised benchmarks, dementia and Alzheimer's prediction competitive with ADNI/OASIS baselines. These are encouraging. They are not a substitute for the core generalizability test: how does Prima perform on routine scans from a community hospital with different equipment, different protocols, and a different patient population?</p>
      <p>The authors acknowledge this. Prima is in what they describe as the "initial stage" of clinical certification. It has not received FDA clearance. It has not been submitted for clearance, as far as the paper or any public statement discloses. It is not deployed in clinical practice. The code and model weights are open-source under an MIT license on GitHub, which means the architecture can be replicated. The dataset cannot. UM220K is Michigan's. Every other hospital that wants to follow this approach would need to build a model from its own archive.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="section" id="signal">
      <h2><span class="num">05 — Signal</span>Can Every Hospital Build Its Own?</h2>
      <p>What Prima proves is specific: a mid-sized research university with twenty years of digitized radiology records and modest high-performance computing resources — eight GPUs, fifty days — can build a specialist diagnostic AI that outperforms every general-purpose model by a wide margin. The ingredients are not exotic compute or a proprietary architecture. They are institutional data and time. The authors report consistent performance improvements with larger training datasets, suggesting foundation model scaling properties. If this holds, hospitals with larger or more diverse archives would build even stronger models.</p>
      <p>The open-source release lowers one barrier. The code is on GitHub. The weights are available. Any institution can study the architecture, adapt the training pipeline, and attempt replication. But the bottleneck is not the method. It is the data. UM220K represents a specific institutional asset — two decades of paired scans and reports from radiologists whose clinical culture, diagnostic vocabulary, and decision patterns are baked into every label. Building an equivalent dataset requires having generated and stored that data in the first place. Most community hospitals do not have twenty years of digitized radiology at this scale. Many do not have the HPC infrastructure either.</p>
      <p>One gap is worth noting: every quote in the coverage of Prima comes from the research team or University of Michigan institutional staff. No independent radiologist or AI researcher has publicly evaluated Prima's claims. The peer review process at <em>Nature Biomedical Engineering</em> provides editorial and reviewer oversight as a partial proxy. The open-source release enables independent replication. But as of this writing, no external evaluation has been published. Hollon has described Prima as a "co-pilot for interpreting medical imaging studies" and, more ambitiously, as "ChatGPT for medical imaging." These framings are aspirational, not descriptive of current capability. Prima is a research result published in a peer-reviewed journal. It is not a product. It is not deployed. Whether the approach scales beyond one institution's walls — whether the template can travel even if the dataset cannot — is the question the paper raises but cannot yet answer.</p>
    </section>

  </div>
</StoryLayout>

<script>
(function () {
  const canvas = document.querySelector('.michigan-brain-mri-canvas') as HTMLCanvasElement | null;
  if (!canvas) return;
  const ctx = canvas.getContext('2d')!;

  const ACC_R = 184, ACC_G = 133, ACC_B = 59;
  const BASE_R = 107, BASE_G = 101, BASE_B = 88;
  const DIM_R = 140, DIM_G = 132, DIM_B = 115;
  const BG_COLOR = getComputedStyle(document.documentElement).getPropertyValue('--bg').trim() || '#f5f0e8';

  let W = 0, H = 0, raf = 0, frame = 0;

  const ro = new ResizeObserver(() => {
    W = canvas.offsetWidth;
    H = canvas.offsetHeight;
    canvas.width = W * devicePixelRatio;
    canvas.height = H * devicePixelRatio;
    ctx.setTransform(devicePixelRatio, 0, 0, devicePixelRatio, 0, 0);
  });
  ro.observe(canvas);

  const prefersReduced = window.matchMedia('(prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)').matches;

  const PHASE_SCATTER_END = 120;
  const PHASE_ALIGN_END = 600;
  const PHASE_CRYSTAL_END = 840;
  const PHASE_HOLD_END = 1020;
  const PHASE_DISSOLVE_END = 1320;
  const CYCLE = 1440;

  const NUM_INNER = 40;
  type InnerNode = { x: number; y: number; vx: number; vy: number; baseAngle: number; baseDist: number; r: number; alpha: number; baseAlpha: number; connections: number; warm: number };
  const innerNodes: InnerNode[] = [];

  const NUM_OUTER = 9;
  type OuterNode = { x: number; y: number; vx: number; vy: number; r: number; alpha: number; angle: number; dist: number };
  const outerNodes: OuterNode[] = [];

  const MAX_STRANDS = 65;
  type Strand = { a: number; b: number; alpha: number; targetAlpha: number; born: number; dying: boolean; deathStart: number };
  const strands: Strand[] = [];

  const BOUNDARY_R = 130;
  const BOUNDARY_PAD = 20;
  let boundaryAlpha = 0.08;
  let interiorGlowAlpha = 0;

  const cxFn = () => W / 2;
  const cyFn = () => H / 2;

  function nodeDist(ax: number, ay: number, bx: number, by: number) {
    const dx = ax - bx, dy = ay - by;
    return Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy);
  }

  function strandExists(a: number, b: number) {
    for (const s of strands) {
      if ((s.a === a && s.b === b) || (s.a === b && s.b === a)) return true;
    }
    return false;
  }

  function initInner() {
    innerNodes.length = 0;
    for (let i = 0; i < NUM_INNER; i++) {
      const angle = Math.random() * Math.PI * 2;
      const d = Math.random() * (BOUNDARY_R - 10);
      innerNodes.push({
        x: cxFn() + Math.cos(angle) * d,
        y: cyFn() + Math.sin(angle) * d,
        vx: (Math.random() - 0.5) * 0.4,
        vy: (Math.random() - 0.5) * 0.4,
        baseAngle: angle,
        baseDist: d,
        r: 2 + Math.random() * 1,
        alpha: 0.25,
        baseAlpha: 0.25,
        connections: 0,
        warm: 0,
      });
    }
  }

  function initOuter() {
    outerNodes.length = 0;
    for (let i = 0; i < NUM_OUTER; i++) {
      const angle = Math.random() * Math.PI * 2;
      const d = BOUNDARY_R + BOUNDARY_PAD + 15 + Math.random() * 50;
      outerNodes.push({
        x: cxFn() + Math.cos(angle) * d,
        y: cyFn() + Math.sin(angle) * d,
        vx: (Math.random() - 0.5) * 0.3,
        vy: (Math.random() - 0.5) * 0.3,
        r: 2,
        alpha: 0.12,
        angle,
        dist: d,
      });
    }
  }

  function resetStrands() { strands.length = 0; }

  function repositionInner() {
    for (const n of innerNodes) {
      const angle = Math.random() * Math.PI * 2;
      const d = Math.random() * (BOUNDARY_R - 10);
      n.x = cxFn() + Math.cos(angle) * d;
      n.y = cyFn() + Math.sin(angle) * d;
      n.vx = (Math.random() - 0.5) * 0.4;
      n.vy = (Math.random() - 0.5) * 0.4;
      n.connections = 0;
      n.warm = 0;
      n.alpha = n.baseAlpha;
    }
  }

  function update() {
    const cf = frame % CYCLE;

    for (const n of innerNodes) {
      n.vx += (Math.random() - 0.5) * 0.04;
      n.vy += (Math.random() - 0.5) * 0.04;
      n.vx *= 0.98;
      n.vy *= 0.98;
      const maxV = 0.4;
      if (n.vx > maxV) n.vx = maxV;
      if (n.vx < -maxV) n.vx = -maxV;
      if (n.vy > maxV) n.vy = maxV;
      if (n.vy < -maxV) n.vy = -maxV;

      n.x += n.vx;
      n.y += n.vy;

      const d = nodeDist(n.x, n.y, cxFn(), cyFn());
      if (d > BOUNDARY_R - 5) {
        const angle = Math.atan2(n.y - cyFn(), n.x - cxFn());
        n.x = cxFn() + Math.cos(angle) * (BOUNDARY_R - 6);
        n.y = cyFn() + Math.sin(angle) * (BOUNDARY_R - 6);
        const nx2 = Math.cos(angle), ny2 = Math.sin(angle);
        const dot = n.vx * nx2 + n.vy * ny2;
        n.vx -= 2 * dot * nx2;
        n.vy -= 2 * dot * ny2;
      }
    }

    for (const n of outerNodes) {
      n.vx += (Math.random() - 0.5) * 0.02;
      n.vy += (Math.random() - 0.5) * 0.02;
      n.vx *= 0.99;
      n.vy *= 0.99;
      const maxV = 0.15;
      if (n.vx > maxV) n.vx = maxV;
      if (n.vx < -maxV) n.vx = -maxV;
      if (n.vy > maxV) n.vy = maxV;
      if (n.vy < -maxV) n.vy = -maxV;

      n.x += n.vx;
      n.y += n.vy;

      const d = nodeDist(n.x, n.y, cxFn(), cyFn());
      if (d < BOUNDARY_R + BOUNDARY_PAD) {
        const angle = Math.atan2(n.y - cyFn(), n.x - cxFn());
        n.x = cxFn() + Math.cos(angle) * (BOUNDARY_R + BOUNDARY_PAD + 2);
        n.y = cyFn() + Math.sin(angle) * (BOUNDARY_R + BOUNDARY_PAD + 2);
        const nx2 = Math.cos(angle), ny2 = Math.sin(angle);
        const dot = n.vx * nx2 + n.vy * ny2;
        n.vx -= 2 * dot * nx2;
        n.vy -= 2 * dot * ny2;
      }
      if (n.x < 10) { n.x = 10; n.vx = Math.abs(n.vx); }
      if (n.x > W - 10) { n.x = W - 10; n.vx = -Math.abs(n.vx); }
      if (n.y < 10) { n.y = 10; n.vy = Math.abs(n.vy); }
      if (n.y > H - 10) { n.y = H - 10; n.vy = -Math.abs(n.vy); }
    }

    for (const n of innerNodes) n.connections = 0;
    for (const s of strands) {
      if (!s.dying) {
        innerNodes[s.a].connections++;
        innerNodes[s.b].connections++;
      }
    }

    if (cf < PHASE_SCATTER_END) {
      boundaryAlpha = 0.08;
      interiorGlowAlpha = 0;
      for (const n of innerNodes) { n.alpha = n.baseAlpha; n.warm = 0; }
    } else if (cf < PHASE_ALIGN_END) {
      const t = (cf - PHASE_SCATTER_END) / (PHASE_ALIGN_END - PHASE_SCATTER_END);
      boundaryAlpha = 0.08 + t * 0.04;

      if ((cf - PHASE_SCATTER_END) % 15 === 0 && strands.length < MAX_STRANDS) {
        let bestA = -1, bestB = -1, bestD = Infinity;
        for (let attempts = 0; attempts < 30; attempts++) {
          const ai = (Math.random() * NUM_INNER) | 0;
          const bi = (Math.random() * NUM_INNER) | 0;
          if (ai === bi) continue;
          const d2 = nodeDist(innerNodes[ai].x, innerNodes[ai].y, innerNodes[bi].x, innerNodes[bi].y);
          if (d2 < 60 && d2 < bestD && !strandExists(ai, bi)) { bestA = ai; bestB = bi; bestD = d2; }
        }
        if (bestA >= 0) {
          strands.push({ a: bestA, b: bestB, alpha: 0, targetAlpha: 0.10 + Math.random() * 0.08, born: cf, dying: false, deathStart: 0 });
        }
      }

      for (const s of strands) { if (!s.dying) s.alpha = Math.min(s.targetAlpha, s.alpha + 0.002); }

      for (const s of strands) {
        if (s.dying) continue;
        const na = innerNodes[s.a], nb = innerNodes[s.b];
        const dx = nb.x - na.x, dy = nb.y - na.y;
        const d2 = Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy) || 1;
        const force = 0.02;
        na.vx += (dx / d2) * force; na.vy += (dy / d2) * force;
        nb.vx -= (dx / d2) * force; nb.vy -= (dy / d2) * force;
      }

      for (const n of innerNodes) {
        if (n.connections >= 3) n.alpha = Math.min(0.4, n.alpha + 0.003);
      }
    } else if (cf < PHASE_CRYSTAL_END) {
      boundaryAlpha = 0.12 + 0.04 * Math.sin(cf * 0.07);
      interiorGlowAlpha = ((cf - PHASE_ALIGN_END) / (PHASE_CRYSTAL_END - PHASE_ALIGN_END)) * 0.06;

      for (const s of strands) {
        if (s.dying) continue;
        const na = innerNodes[s.a], nb = innerNodes[s.b];
        const dx = nb.x - na.x, dy = nb.y - na.y;
        const d2 = Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy) || 1;
        const force = 0.035;
        na.vx += (dx / d2) * force; na.vy += (dy / d2) * force;
        nb.vx -= (dx / d2) * force; nb.vy -= (dy / d2) * force;
        s.alpha = Math.min(s.targetAlpha, s.alpha + 0.003);
      }

      for (const n of innerNodes) {
        if (n.connections >= 4) {
          n.warm = Math.min(1, n.warm + 0.02);
          n.alpha = Math.min(0.6, n.alpha + 0.005);
        } else if (n.connections >= 2) {
          n.warm = Math.min(0.4, n.warm + 0.008);
          n.alpha = Math.min(0.45, n.alpha + 0.003);
        }
      }

      if (cf % 8 === 0 && strands.length < MAX_STRANDS) {
        let bestA = -1, bestB = -1, bestD = Infinity;
        for (let attempts = 0; attempts < 40; attempts++) {
          const ai = (Math.random() * NUM_INNER) | 0;
          const bi = (Math.random() * NUM_INNER) | 0;
          if (ai === bi) continue;
          const d2 = nodeDist(innerNodes[ai].x, innerNodes[ai].y, innerNodes[bi].x, innerNodes[bi].y);
          if (d2 < 70 && d2 < bestD && !strandExists(ai, bi)) { bestA = ai; bestB = bi; bestD = d2; }
        }
        if (bestA >= 0) {
          strands.push({ a: bestA, b: bestB, alpha: 0, targetAlpha: 0.12 + Math.random() * 0.06, born: cf, dying: false, deathStart: 0 });
        }
      }
    } else if (cf < PHASE_HOLD_END) {
      boundaryAlpha = 0.12 + 0.04 * Math.sin(cf * 0.07);
      interiorGlowAlpha = 0.06;

      for (const n of innerNodes) {
        n.x += Math.sin(cf * 0.03 + n.baseAngle) * 0.15;
        n.y += Math.cos(cf * 0.03 + n.baseDist * 0.01) * 0.15;
      }

      for (const s of strands) { if (!s.dying) s.alpha = Math.min(s.targetAlpha, s.alpha + 0.001); }

      for (const s of strands) {
        if (s.dying) continue;
        const na = innerNodes[s.a], nb = innerNodes[s.b];
        const dx = nb.x - na.x, dy = nb.y - na.y;
        const d2 = Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy) || 1;
        const force = 0.015;
        na.vx += (dx / d2) * force; na.vy += (dy / d2) * force;
        nb.vx -= (dx / d2) * force; nb.vy -= (dy / d2) * force;
      }
    } else if (cf < PHASE_DISSOLVE_END) {
      const t = (cf - PHASE_HOLD_END) / (PHASE_DISSOLVE_END - PHASE_HOLD_END);
      boundaryAlpha = 0.12 - t * 0.04;
      interiorGlowAlpha = 0.06 * (1 - t);

      for (let i = 0; i < strands.length; i++) {
        const s = strands[i];
        if (s.dying) continue;
        const na = innerNodes[s.a], nb = innerNodes[s.b];
        const avgD = (nodeDist(na.x, na.y, cxFn(), cyFn()) + nodeDist(nb.x, nb.y, cxFn(), cyFn())) / 2;
        const normalizedDist = avgD / BOUNDARY_R;
        if (t > normalizedDist * 0.7) { s.dying = true; s.deathStart = cf; }
      }

      for (const s of strands) {
        if (s.dying) {
          const elapsed = cf - s.deathStart;
          s.alpha = Math.max(0, s.targetAlpha * (1 - elapsed / 40));
        }
      }

      for (const n of innerNodes) {
        n.warm = Math.max(0, n.warm - 0.015);
        n.alpha = Math.max(n.baseAlpha, n.alpha - 0.004);
      }
    } else {
      boundaryAlpha = 0.08;
      interiorGlowAlpha = 0;

      for (const n of innerNodes) { n.warm = 0; n.alpha = n.baseAlpha; }
      for (const s of strands) { s.alpha = Math.max(0, s.alpha - 0.01); }

      if (cf === CYCLE - 1) { repositionInner(); resetStrands(); }
    }

    for (let i = strands.length - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
      if (strands[i].alpha <= 0 && strands[i].dying) strands.splice(i, 1);
    }
  }

  function draw() {
    ctx.fillStyle = BG_COLOR;
    ctx.fillRect(0, 0, W, H);

    if (interiorGlowAlpha > 0.001) {
      const grad = ctx.createRadialGradient(cxFn(), cyFn(), 0, cxFn(), cyFn(), BOUNDARY_R);
      grad.addColorStop(0, `rgba(${ACC_R},${ACC_G},${ACC_B},${(interiorGlowAlpha * 1.5).toFixed(4)})`);
      grad.addColorStop(0.6, `rgba(${ACC_R},${ACC_G},${ACC_B},${(interiorGlowAlpha * 0.6).toFixed(4)})`);
      grad.addColorStop(1, `rgba(${ACC_R},${ACC_G},${ACC_B},0)`);
      ctx.fillStyle = grad;
      ctx.beginPath();
      ctx.arc(cxFn(), cyFn(), BOUNDARY_R, 0, Math.PI * 2);
      ctx.fill();
    }

    ctx.beginPath();
    ctx.arc(cxFn(), cyFn(), BOUNDARY_R + BOUNDARY_PAD, 0, Math.PI * 2);
    ctx.strokeStyle = `rgba(${ACC_R},${ACC_G},${ACC_B},${boundaryAlpha.toFixed(3)})`;
    ctx.lineWidth = 1;
    ctx.stroke();

    ctx.lineWidth = 0.8;
    for (const s of strands) {
      if (s.alpha <= 0.001) continue;
      const na = innerNodes[s.a], nb = innerNodes[s.b];
      ctx.beginPath();
      ctx.moveTo(na.x, na.y);
      ctx.lineTo(nb.x, nb.y);
      ctx.strokeStyle = `rgba(${ACC_R},${ACC_G},${ACC_B},${s.alpha.toFixed(3)})`;
      ctx.stroke();
    }

    for (const n of innerNodes) {
      const wr = Math.round(BASE_R + (ACC_R - BASE_R) * n.warm);
      const wg = Math.round(BASE_G + (ACC_G - BASE_G) * n.warm);
      const wb = Math.round(BASE_B + (ACC_B - BASE_B) * n.warm);

      ctx.globalAlpha = n.alpha * 0.25;
      ctx.fillStyle = `rgb(${wr},${wg},${wb})`;
      ctx.beginPath();
      ctx.arc(n.x, n.y, n.r * 2.5, 0, Math.PI * 2);
      ctx.fill();

      ctx.globalAlpha = n.alpha;
      ctx.fillStyle = `rgb(${wr},${wg},${wb})`;
      ctx.beginPath();
      ctx.arc(n.x, n.y, n.r, 0, Math.PI * 2);
      ctx.fill();
    }
    ctx.globalAlpha = 1;

    for (const n of outerNodes) {
      ctx.globalAlpha = n.alpha * 0.3;
      ctx.fillStyle = `rgb(${DIM_R},${DIM_G},${DIM_B})`;
      ctx.beginPath();
      ctx.arc(n.x, n.y, n.r * 2, 0, Math.PI * 2);
      ctx.fill();

      ctx.globalAlpha = n.alpha;
      ctx.fillStyle = `rgb(${DIM_R},${DIM_G},${DIM_B})`;
      ctx.beginPath();
      ctx.arc(n.x, n.y, n.r, 0, Math.PI * 2);
      ctx.fill();
    }
    ctx.globalAlpha = 1;
  }

  function drawStatic() {
    for (let i = 0; i < NUM_INNER; i++) {
      const n = innerNodes[i];
      const angle = (i / NUM_INNER) * Math.PI * 2 + Math.sin(i * 0.7) * 0.5;
      const ring = (i % 4) / 4;
      const r = 20 + ring * (BOUNDARY_R - 30);
      n.x = cxFn() + Math.cos(angle) * r;
      n.y = cyFn() + Math.sin(angle) * r;
      n.warm = (i % 3 === 0) ? 0.85 : 0.35;
      n.alpha = 0.5;
      n.connections = 3;
    }

    resetStrands();
    for (let i = 0; i < NUM_INNER; i++) {
      for (let j = i + 1; j < NUM_INNER; j++) {
        if (strands.length >= MAX_STRANDS) break;
        const d2 = nodeDist(innerNodes[i].x, innerNodes[i].y, innerNodes[j].x, innerNodes[j].y);
        if (d2 < 65) {
          strands.push({ a: i, b: j, alpha: 0.14, targetAlpha: 0.14, born: 0, dying: false, deathStart: 0 });
        }
      }
      if (strands.length >= MAX_STRANDS) break;
    }

    for (let i = 0; i < NUM_OUTER; i++) {
      const n = outerNodes[i];
      const angle = (i / NUM_OUTER) * Math.PI * 2 + 0.3;
      const d = BOUNDARY_R + BOUNDARY_PAD + 20 + (i % 3) * 20;
      n.x = cxFn() + Math.cos(angle) * d;
      n.y = cyFn() + Math.sin(angle) * d;
    }

    boundaryAlpha = 0.14;
    interiorGlowAlpha = 0.06;
    draw();
  }

  function tick() { frame++; update(); draw(); raf = requestAnimationFrame(tick); }

  function init() { initInner(); initOuter(); resetStrands(); }

  requestAnimationFrame(() => {
    init();
    if (prefersReduced) {
      drawStatic();
    } else {
      const io = new IntersectionObserver(([e]) => {
        if (e.isIntersecting) { if (!raf) raf = requestAnimationFrame(tick); }
        else { cancelAnimationFrame(raf); raf = 0; }
      }, { threshold: 0.01 });
      io.observe(canvas);

      window.addEventListener('pagehide', () => { cancelAnimationFrame(raf); io.disconnect(); ro.disconnect(); });
    }
  });
})();
</script>
